= Publishing Stable SDS Version

In the fifth and final stage, The Product Owner confirms the finalisation of the latest release candidate of a specific ePO version as a stable release. Consequently, the SDS and SDS documentation of the specific candidate are marked accordingly, and the new ePO stable release is announced.

The detailed business workflow for the Publishing Stable SDS Version Stage is depicted in the diagram below.



image::publishing stable SDS version [detailed].bmp[]
_The Publishing Stable SDS Version Business view diagram_


The business workflow with Stakeholders for the Publishing Stable SDS Version Stage is depicted in the diagram below:


image::publishing stable SDS version [stakeholders].bmp[]


_The Publishing Stable SDS Version with stakeholders business view diagram._


In the “*Decide to release*” Business Process, the Product Owner decides to release the latest ePO version release candidate as a stable release.

in the "*Tag the final SDS release*" Business Process, the Product Owner creates a release tag on the same commit as the latest release candidate tag on the https://github.com/OP-TED/ePO[OP-TED/ePO] repository.

in the "*Publish final SDS release*" Business Process, The GitHub pre-release flag is unchecked by the Product Owner, making the release stable as seen in the figure below:

image::data:image/png;base64,[]
_The v4.2.0-rc1 tag is currently set as a pre-release tag. To change it, just click at the checkbox “Set as the latest release” at the bottom of the screen._

in the "*Tag the final SDS documentation release*" Business Process, the Product Owner creates a release tag on the same commit as the latest release candidate tag on the https://github.com/OP-TED/epo-docs[OP-TED/epo-docs] repository.



In the “*Publish the final SDS documentation release*” Business Process, the Product Owner removes the “rc” suffix from the asciidoc pages of the documentation on the release/x.y.z branch of the https://github.com/OP-TED/epo-docs[OP-TED/epo-docs] repository. Consequently, the Documentation Website must be regenerated again to reflect this change.


In the "*The stable version is merged from release into master*" Business Process, the Product Owner merges the release into the Master branch of the https://github.com/OP-TED/ePO[OP-TED/ePO] repository.

In the “Announce the release of the stable version” the Product Owner:

* Announces the release to the wider working group.

* Announces and Publishes the release on https://interoperable-europe.ec.europa.eu/collection/eprocurement/solution/eprocurement-ontology[Interoperable Europe].

* Submits the OWL files of the release to https://op.europa.eu/en/web/cellar[Cellar] for publication.

* Submits the release to https://op.europa.eu/en/web/eu-vocabularies[EU Vocabularies] for publication to the https://op.europa.eu/en/web/eu-vocabularies/e-procurement[eProcurement business collection].


== Application and Technology view

The diagram below displays only the artefacts updated in this stage using the business (yellow), application (blue) and technology (green) layers. The GitHub Repository branch that is used for this stage is also depicted as an orange rectangle for reference purposes. The only content that is changed during this stage is the “SDS documentation” artefact as the “rc” mark is removed from all the documents containing the "rc" mark. In order for this change to be displayed online, the “eProcurement Ontology staging website” and “eProcurement Ontology website” data objects must be regenerated by following the same process as the one described in xref:Business Process workflow/stage4/stage4.adoc[stage 4].
